  "text": "As discussed in Section 3, instances can satisfy the assumptions of the DDGP 3 if a suitable reordering for its atoms is found. The problem of finding vertex orders for a given graph G for which the assumptions are satisfied has been widely discussed in [CITATION_1] . In this paper, we only point out that, given an instance that does not belong to the class of the DDGP 3 , its vertex reordering may generate an instance for which the necessary assumptions are instead satisfied.",
